      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and finely slice<strong> half</strong> your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining onion</strong> into small wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684229572110-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684229572110-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684229572110-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684229572110-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1684229572110-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a large piece of<strong> tin foil</strong> with your<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Scrunch the foil around the onion wedges to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to one side of a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684229577098-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684229577098-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684229577098-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684229577098-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1684229577098-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 10 min, remove the baking tray from the oven and add the <strong>crispy chicken</strong> to the other side of the baking tray (skin side up)</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the onion is softened and jammy – these are your <strong>balsamic onions </strong>(save the juices)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684229582376-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684229582376-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684229582376-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684229582376-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1684229582376-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to the pan with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684229587138-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684229587138-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684229587138-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684229587138-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1684229587138-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>orzo</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>spicy tomato orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684229593159-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684229593159-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684229593159-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684229593159-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684229593159-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy tomato orzo</strong> with the<strong> crispy chicken</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>balsamic onions</strong> on top</p><p>Toss the <strong>salad</strong> with the <strong>remaining balsamic onions</strong> and a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, then serve to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
